caption: Second time coming. I had a Manhattan and a strip steak. Both were awesome.

One of the best places in Buffalo! Little on the pricey side but worth it. Food is amazing, huge whiskey selection, great whiskey cocktails (but they also have a full bar if you don't like whiskey), and the staff is very friendly and welcoming.
Not just for whiskey lovers! Ambiance is welcoming and historic while maintaining a modern feel. Unique to say the least!
Amazing atmosphere, phenomenal selection

My girlfriend and I just went for a little while and we happened to hit their happy hour which they apparently run everyday from 4 - 6 and you can get either $6 Manhattan's or old fashioned's along with either $6 fried chicken sandwiches or burgers, all of which were great!
Great whiskey selection. Food was decent. They do a great job separating tables
Whyskey heaven. Great food.

Wonderful little place. The whiskey flight was totally worth it. The happy hour drinks were tasty and a great deal. I got the lucky day bacon and it was delicious. Both bartenders were very friendly gentleman who knew a lot about the products. They do more that whiskey! My friend got a white russian, she was very pleased with it. Excellent drinks. Reasonable prices, although bear in mind it's a high end whiskey bar so there are some pricey options available.
Wonderful ambiance. Great bartenders. Good food and flights
I mean its the best whisky bar in upstate NY. What more of a recommendation do you need.
Really want to go here
Awesome cocktails
Awesome bartenders! Very knowledgeable and make incredible drinks!
Best whiskey sour!
Everytime I get food here I am blown away by how delicious it is. Also, awesome whiskey selection.
Always a delicious meal here--even the Brussels sprouts are amazing. Staff is always friendly, atmosphere is swanky and relaxed. And the most incredible bourbon selection I've ever seen!
LOVE this place! Awesome atmosphere, drinks and food!!!
Great food, awesome drinks, amazing music
Great place to chill and have a nice drink with friends. My one complaint was that I wish they had better choices for appetizers. It was just oysters and pickles. Kind of odd drinking food.
Love the setup at the bar!  You're able to be socially distant and yet still enjoy the bar feeling! Great night. Thanks!
Great place awesome bartenders  very knowledgeable!
Superb selection and knowledge of fine bourbon and whiskey. Dinner was phenomenal with our party being impressed with the steak and chicken entrees followed by exquisite desserts.
Visited pre covid. Loved it. The bartenders are knowledgeable and the drinks are amazing. The prices are much lower then I would have guessed.

The young lady at the front desk of the Hyatt hotel across the street recommended this for a cocktail .... it's a 15 second walk away. This place has a phenomenal whiskey selection and a terrific cocktail menu. I went with a Sazerac and was perfectly satisfied!! Certainly not the cheapest cocktail around but wonderful bar tenders along with the selection make this a great cocktail choice.
I love this place.
Love their cocktails, cant beat the whiskey/bourbon/rye selection! Will have to come back for a bite to eat someday... also, how can you not love a bar with a portait of a cat holding a dead rabbit?
Oh.My.Yum. Chase tended to our beverage and food needs, and everything was top notch.
the only bad thing about this place is the acoustics. everything else is bangin- food, drink, ambiance. the curtained downstairs tables? chef's kiss.
I adore this place. Love the concept and atmosphere. Best whiskey drinks in Buffalo. Service is top notch.

Super cool Whiskey Bar with an Irish/German style menu and decor. I ordered hand pies and a pickle plate and would highly recommend both. Reasonably priced and menu online and can even make reservations on there too for convenience if you're like me and want to look before you show up!
Liked the atmosphere with all the people and the live music. I tried the gouda mac and cheese then the chicken and waffles. Both were excellent.
Very simple menu. Amazing vibe and style tho. Good drinks
Fun bar!

Stopped in for dinner.  Service was good but it was hard to hear our server because the music was pretty loud.  Overall, the drinks were fantastic, chicken and waffles appetizer was amazing.  Entrees (steak/lobster and bourbon glazed chicken) were good but nothing to write home about.  Whiskey selection was expansive and the menu was broken down nicely by type and region.
Great bourbons,  I mean anything you have ever wished to try. Food very good as well.
Their ice cubes have their name stamped into it. So many options it's literally crazy. Good for a casual drink or a fancy business meeting. Stay classy buffalo
Great cocktails and great food. The pies are delicious especially the duck wings a must try. Also try the scotch eggs. My favorite  is the short rib stroganoff.

As a new establishment in Buffalo It is incredible - the staff is friendly- food is awesome Service is 10 out of 10 Drink selection is unbelievable as well I would highly recommend this hidden jewel to anyone

Best whiskey selection around, including a fairly good japanese collection. I like the fact that they set the bottle in front of you at the bar so you can examine and read the bottle, nice touch. Got the burger and mac n cheese, pretty large portions and tasted good. Great service and good conversation with the bartenders, reasonable prices

This place makes whiskey sours the correct way with the egg white, which not all bars do.  Also whoever they got for the live music was great, instead of just covering popular songs they put their own unique twist on it.
Love this place.the atmosphere, cocktails and food.

I've popped in here a couple times now. I spent some time at the bar which was very lively. The prices very wildly depending on what you order, but overall tends to be pretty expensive. The first cocktail I ordered I enjoyed. I enjoyed it so much that I ordered it a second time, but the second time it came it was prepared differently and was noticeably worse. Almost as if an ingredient had been forgotten. When I'm paying so much for a single cocktail I expect it to be perfect every single time.  The food is pretty good. It's basically upscale pub food.  The atmosphere is definitely what would keep me coming back. It has a very cool old buffalo feel. Almost a factory turned speakeasy in the night feel.
Good drinks and great whiskey selection.

Liberty Hound was my 2019 Restaurant Week pick of the week. It is tradition for me to always make sure I get to at least one restaurant though I happily visit more if I am able. I had a decent level of expectation knowing how popular this place is, especially with it being right in the heart of Canalside. It is always overflowing with happy commotion on summer nights with patio dining on the water and live music sometimes either hosted here or nearby.

Expansive whiskey menu (duh) and fantastic bartending staff. Cool atmosphere and live music. I had a Sazerac which was delicious. Highly recommend checking this place put at least once even if you're not a whiskey fan and let them staff suggest something new for you to try.
Great place to meet for a drink! Amazing atmosphere. Good prices
AWESOME buck-a-shuck oyster specials

Stopped in to this establishment for a cocktail Fri night around 10 pm 01/03/2020. Bar area was very crowded restaurant area was very quite so after getting a drink from the bar I took a seat at a table to watch the band that was playing and was approached buy a rude hostess who told me i could not sit at the table when i asked why she got an attitude with me so i told her i wanted to talk to the manager. The woman mng on that night came up to me and told me and asked what the problem way i said there was no problem we were just having some drinks and watching the band she went on to tell me that we could not sit at the table they were for dinner guests only!!! I said there is 30 empty tables and 3 TABLES eating she didn't care just flat out RUDE. So if planning to visiting this place make sure you understand what area you allowed in and which you are not I would have stayed for a few more drinks if they would have just let me sit in the EMPTY dinning area but apparently that a BIG no  I will not return to this place ever again

Neat bar/restaurant.  Steak with coffee rub was decent and unique.  Lobster and Gouda Mac and cheese were excellent.  Brownie with peanut butter ice cream was great.  Chicken and waffle appetizer was good.  Service was decent.  Good whiskey and bourbon selection.
Awesome place if you like some good choices and some good live music
It's a little oasis of class downtown. A lovely bar to enjoy a wide variety of whiskey. I had a great time, and will come again
What a fantastic bar with live music! The staff were super friendly. This is must whenever in the City of Buffalo.

Whiskeys you've never heard of? Check. A warm atmosphere? Check. Loud but not so loud you cant hear the person next to you talking music? Check. Oysters sourced from nova Scotia? I dunno about always but the night I went....check. Everything's on the pricey side but that's about par for downtown buffalo and the plus to it all is the burger knows what it's doing and it's doing it well (not too big, and the chef picks the toppings, which in my particular case made for a fun experience; the chef nailed it with a slice of thick bacon and mushrooms). I will definitely be going back and while the color palette is your typical hipster/yuppie brown, and I mean brown...the bar the lights the walls etc...warm but ubiquitous broooown, the ambiance and sophisticated flavors more than make up for it. Easily recommend it.
Like it hear.  Fun place
Incredible library of whiskey. Unmatched bartenders and atmosphere. The live music is always fantastic.

A popular bar in the City of Buffalo. It doesnt look like much from the outside but the inside is very inviting with a warm and friendly atmosphere. With a huge bar area.  The drinks and food are delicious.  I was drinking Manhattans with Sweet Vermouth.  I would reccomend making a reservation if you plan on eating dinner there, you don't need one, but it does fill up fast. I would definitely go back again.
Great bloody Mary!
Great staff, wonderful drinks

Every once in a while, one encounters a restaurant that does such a good job, they deserve a second positive review. The Lucky Day is one such place. It's a very attractive barroom that one feels immediately comfortable in. The whisky selection is amazingly broad and deep. During happy hour 6.00 will buy you an old fashioned or a Manhattan, plus there are freshly shucked oysters for a dollar a piece. A very solid menu rounds out the food side. Service at the bar was 5 star. I would not pass through Buffalo and miss an opportunity to visit the Lucky Day. Well done for sure.
Bartenders were very helpful in terms of suggestions of different whiskeys, being a newcomer to whiskey I had a great time experiencing different tastes
Great bourbon menu and delicious food.  Very cool bar area and exciting atmosphere.
Great bourbon selection
Best Whiskey bar in 10 towns, hands downs. Huge selection, fair prices, top shelf ambience, and high grade materials/workmanship throughout for an all-around VERY pleasant experience.
loud music and slow service
Great  Atmosphere and good whiskey and great music and Friday night
Amazing bartenders.  Awsome security guard. Great food and drinks...
Love this place. Great music and drinks. The bartenders are awesome.

Once inside, the place is very dim, but small alcoves of booths and tables are more brightly lit. Walls are exposed brick and beautiful woodwork separates each area of the place into a nice bar space, and more intimate seating. A large Buffalo head watches over the place from the front, and knowledgeable bartenders will whip up any drink on the menu, or even their own creation with bourbon or whiskey.
Very good wings.
Great selection
Atmosphere great, great drinks

Great selection of whiskey/scotch but CHASE the bartender has no clue about anything scotch. I consider myself a food and fine drink specialist at it's worst. I asked this gentleman quite a fee questions and he couldn't answer one of them without running to his screen of knowledge. Told him smokey wasn't a option and yet smokey is all he could offer. Don't blow smoke hood sir when you know little. Your service has gone smokey.  EDIT: A friend I was with ended up saying something to Frank, the other tender. He completely saved the day.. well educated! Returned with a sample of perfections.  Revised original review fro. m 1 to 3 stars from original. Will return to edit/add.
Interesting menu, great drinks!
Went for restaurant week. Service was great and drinks were delicious. The hand pie was AMAZING.   We also had the steak which was just okay. I will definitely come back again for hand pies
All I can say. Wall of whiskeys .

Come for the whiskey--stay for the food, and the atmosphere, and the live music, and the warmth. The shepherds pie and the bone-in pork chop are two of the best dishes I've had in Buffalo. Highly suggest this location for anyone looking to impress their visiting friends/family.

The food was inscrutable and the service impeccable. I don't know what else to say...oh wait...lobster tail and lamb pops were perfectly prepared, as were the sides. I'll be back for sure! 😋 And very inexpensive.
amazing service with great vibes
Great food, perfect atmosphere. Band was fantastic. Quaint decor with a little class and a little sass. Try it. You have a great evening.
Whiskey, need I say more?
Incredible whiskey selection with really knowledgeable bartenders.
Great service, food and drink selection

Have a shellfish allergy be and while making me drink the bartender decided to stop and clean up oysters from another person (super unprofessional). The bartender then comes back to making our drinks and doesn't wash his hands! I politely told him about this and he gave serious attitude and then decided to make jokes about it! I've been to this bar many other times and have had great experiences but won't be back again. This bartender was as unprofessional as they come!
Great place for some good times.
Great food. Water is always warm and it's always too warm inside
Cocktails and service great. Food lacking.
Old school, classic bar. A throwback in time.
HUGE selection! Very friendly & helpful staff! Makes a REAL old fashioned!
Excellent food and atmosphere
Awesome atmosphere. Small menu but absolutely delicious!

Great spot to end the evening. Very good whiskey & bourbon selection along with many other imbibements that might fit anyone's appetite. Had a really good chicken po boy as well. Staff is knowledgeable, friendly and very professional. I will definitely visit again. When I do I really hope they have love music again. That really made the night.
Amazing selection of whiskey and great specials. Food was also good.
Nice bar
Amazing food
These bartenders have such amazing knowledge and expertise!
Very cool bar and nice cocktails. It's a big place with plenty of room to stand around if the bar is full. Though it gets very loud when it's busy.
Food was really good with nice twists on classic entrees. Drinks were on point, with possibly more whiskey options than you could drink in a lifetime.
Went on a date night with friends and it was delicious and fun. Great atmosphere.
Awesome ambiance and selection
A great spot to enjoy a late night cocktail! Over 600 bottles, so lots of options! It's a dark bar with comfortable seating, and occasional live music.

Was my first time at Lucky day and enjoyed it . Probably the largest selection of whiskey in the area. The bar is slightly upscale in dress, and makes for a fun atmosphere. The bartenders were great and attentive. Will be back again soon
The food was killer the drinks were very good and the service was exceptional.
Amazing atmosphere great service incredible food
Cool vibe.  Worth a stop if near by.
Insane bourbon collection with gnarly food options. Let's see how long it takes to try everything.
Drinks were good
Pricy for what you get.....bar is cool looking though.....
It is a library of scotch whiskey and a place to feel fancy. The bartenders here are expert craftsmen and know their artform to the tee.
Great Happy Hour from 4-6 $1 Oysters, $5 Burger. $5 Manhattans....yum
A must stop if in area. Awesome building. Biggest selection of quality spirits I have ever seen. Good food & good service.
Excellent selection, great atmosphere
Everything is excellent!!
Great vibe. Great food. Excellent music.
Amazing selection of cocktails and good food
Great craft cocktails!
Great whisky selections. The must try is beat salad and Mac n cheese. I swear you'll love it.
Very pleasant. Bartenders were nice. Suprisied how busy it was though for a Wednesday

Came here to celebrate getting married. Bar was slammed for happy hour, restaurant was empty. Came here because we saw all the openings on open table and we were excited to try! Got a cool deal on great old fashioneds, and we were excited for the live band, but band doesn't start till 9-10 at night? Then after sitting and drinking for a while and noone asking if we want a table, we go to hostess and ask for a table. She walks us over to the one right next to the slammed bar, is this ok? I say, Can we sit in the booths, she goes NO, those are reserved. Can we sit upstairs? No noone is up there sorry. Finishing up my meal, mostly cold, waiter had the weirdest dryest personality and was maybe his first day? Then I notice as we're finishing up, all the "reserved" booths are still empty? And now there's a bunch of people eating up stairs? Beautiful night not ruined, but not helped, I'd pass, Osteria right next door, or just pay more to enjoy the view from the Curtis!

A great whiskey bar with knowledgeable and accommodating bartenders. They have an extensive inventory, you can enjoy the familiar and never had libations of your choice. I was told it's a local ordnance, all Buffalo bars must have a bison.
Great
Hand pies are a MUST
Limited menu. The lucky day burger was cooked to order. Gouda Mac and cheese with bacon was tasty and cheesy. Sooo good I didn't take a photo till the end of my whiskey flight special.
Who doesn't love whisky? Oh that's right... All the lame people. That's why this bar is awesome.
Awesome whiskey selection and cool hangout spot. $5 burger not too shabby either

It was a good bar, but definitely not a cocktail "experience", as pretentious as that sounds.  We waited about 20 minutes for a table on a Saturday evening and had a great time once we were seated. Our waiter was professional and spry.  Small bar area compared to the dining room. Great atmosphere and aesthetic.
Great selection of whiskey, drinks are well crafted so service is sometimes understandably slow. Beer list is good too
Drinks were great. Burger was absolutely INCREDIBLE!! The best meal I've ever had!
It was ok. Food is good. The band on Saturday night have been there every Saturday and they act it. The looked bored which made us bored...

Food was delicious. Tried the burgers, fresh oysters, sausage & steak. The whiskey selection is ridiculous. Had Japanese whiskey for the first time. A scotch flight and Jefferson Ocean. It was a wonderful experience looking forward to going back.
Great selection of whiskey. Knowledgeable staff and great service.

Excellent beer, a wall of whiskey.  The most tragically hipster environment you could ask for including bunned, tattooed, bearded bar tenders.  I mean what more could you ask for but some funky live music.  Highly recommend, often standing room only.
Excellent Happy Hour ever day till 6......great variety of whiskeys
The food was delicious, the service expeditious, and overall we had a stellar time. Thank you. I'll definitely come back.

One of the best whiskey selections in Buffalo, and their mixed drinks are top notch. Love the paintings and wallpapers used through the place. Intimate dining atmosphere and overall great bar. Staff is always friendly and willing to give a suggestion when looking to try something new.

Of course a great selection of whiskey and other spirits.  Hard to choose but the bartenders can make recommendations.  Food was good and large portions if you're hungry! Menu shows gluten free options if you need them (though there's only a couple and I didn't see any main entrees).
Extensive whiskey selection. Food is great too. Owners are awesome too.
Great selection of whiskey. Good to start the night

This place was great! We had a large party and had reservations. We did family style and loved everything we had! The duck wings appetizer was delicious, but super spicy!! The squash and brussel sprouts were amazing!! We had red wine, so I can't say much about the whiskey drinks.

Lucky day is a very comfortable upscale place. Not unlike Buffalo proper, or like Vera back in it's hayday. But somehow it's a little more comfortable. Even with being packed in like sardines on a Saturday night and having a long wait for drinks, the atmosphere and live music made up for it. And the drinks of course. Such care put into them and a  very extensive selection. Whiskey lovers can really get lost in what they have.
Great vibe, live music. Excellent food!

A very nice place, old school ambiance, aesthetically pleasing  a very long bar with great drinks. Service was fantastic and food was delicious. Recommend the booths for dinning, its like your own little dinning room. Definitely going again.

The best part of this place is the dollar oysters at the bar from 3-6 everyday. That’s right- not just Mon-Fri but Sat and Sun, too! The bar is incredibly stoked from floor to ceiling, and I adore the wooden ladder on wheels, that glides across it for easy access to the top shelves. The bar staff is dressed in adorable vests, and while that shouldn’t be a draw in an of itself, it is. The decor is dark and moody- perfect for a wintertime meal or a few smooth drinks. I place a lot of stock in the decor, and was thrilled that they had leather couches in the front bar section to sit in, and nice touches like a large bison head, bold printed wallpapers, and thick wooden beams.  I went recently for my birthday, and they were able to accomodate a large group of 12, and were incredibly nice and thoughtful during service. We didn’t feel rushed, and they let us linger for hours at our table. They also let us bring our own cake! I had such a lovely time, I cannot recommend it enough. The vibe was great, and we got to hear a live band from the upper floor. Also, the drinks are STRONG!

If all you care about is whiskey selection this is the place for it. A bit overcrowded. With all the drunk bartenders hanging half off  of ladders with no fall  support this place is begging for an OSHA visit. The menu is extensive and there wasn't a whiskey I wanted that they didn't have. I won't go out of my way for this spot but I'd hit it up if I were in the area.

The salads are always great here. I've had the caesar which is highly authentic as well as the house which is a very full mix of greens and some pickled onions on top.  The roasted chicken and elk we're also both really good although I think I liked the chicken more.  They have an extensive selection of beers and whiskey; the real draw to this place.  Not open on Sundays or Mondays from what I remember. Worth going for the ambiance and music. Highly recommended.
Great food and service
Awesome.
Great bourbon and scotch selection and very helpful/friendly staff
The atmosphere cannot be beat...warm, historic...wood beams...great drinks! Try the beet salad, so fresh and delicious! Love it!
Great bar with a wonderful atmosphere.

In downtown Buffalo, the place is right across the old Genesee Building, which is now the Hyatt Hotel. They have an amazing assortment of whiskeys and bourbons.  The day I went there they had a live jazz band.  The atmosphere is inviting and warm.  They have other liquor there as well, but why else would you go to a whiskey bar?

Wow this is the perfect example of a great whiskey bar. Huge selection. Knowledgeable and competent bartenders. Exquisite design. Quality food menu. This place had a wonderful historic feel to it, and you can tell every detail had been thoroughly thought out, from the elegant and timely lighting fixtures, the dark wood, the classy seating, and even down to the brass tacks. The super old refrigerators are cool. The level of detail is impeccable. Highly, highly recommend. Best treasure in Buffalo.
Creative and delicious food.  Great whiskey menu!  Staff is knowledgeable and helpful.  Really good music too.  A must!
Serenity..Excellent Oysters
The largest collection of whiskey, bourbon, and scotch I've ever seen in one location.  The bartenders were great and the patrons we're very nice as well
Classy place and have gluten free potions  tons of drinks for fair prices.
Really good drinks.
Just what this traveler was looking for!
Fantastic whiskey selection with a very knowledgeable staff!  Good happy hour specials as well!
Great time with friends. Amazing selection.
Good old fashioned
Great food, drinks, and music.
Ask for the whiskey sour.

Hands down one of if not the best whiskey bars on the east coast, and certainly the best in Buffalo. Super knowledgeable staff that are super accommodating, great food to complement delicious drinks, and a whiskey selection that will make your head spin. Hands on ownership that is usually there making sure your time is amazing, this is the kind of place you'll tell your grandkids you had the pleasure of enjoying. A true whiskey drinkers destination if you live in NY or the surrounding areas of Buffalo.
Service was terrible.  Slow to get a table. Slow to get drinks and slow to place an order for food.  If you're willing to wait four hours for your food, then you'll be okay with Lucky Day.
Thought I was going for whiskey, but the food was banging!!!!!!! Amazing riveted. Best onion rings ever. Short rib pie was phenomenal.
Great place, excellent food and drinks, Megan was our waitress and she was very friendly and attentive.
Great drinks. I went on a Friday night at 7 and didn't have to wait too long at the bar, considering the delicious drinks take way too long to make.

This place is very cool. Awesome trendy restaurant that obviously takes the time to offer quality food and drinks. The whiskey menu is extensive and the food prices are very fair. We sat in a private booth with curtains on a busy night. We walked in with no reservations and were seated right away. They had a blues band that was pretty good. The whole experience felt unique and authentic. Although it felt like I should have waxed my mustache before walking in the crowd and wait staff were all really cool and friendly. I have been to other places with similar menus where the crowd and staff carry a pretentious attitude. This was not the case in my experience so I gave a 5 star review. I would definitely recommend this restaurant and would love to return if I'm in the area again.
Great cocktails, enormous selection of whiskeys.
Good music and ambience
Absolutely gorgeous, amazing staff.
Great service

Amazing selection of whiskey and scotch.  Was pleasantly surprised when I came in this place.  Bartenders were nice, well informed, and more then happy to help me pick a whiskey.  Food was also great.  Would highly recommend a visit for anyone who likes whiskey or scotch.
Excellent place. Very authentic. Takes you back. Food, drinks, service all excellent!
Great food, band and atmosphere
intense whiskey selection with friendly, knowledgeable and sharply dressed staff as well as live music!
Best happy hour in the area. Alot of attention to detail of your cocktail.
Good spot with great selection of drinks.
Great food. Great service. Great Wednesday night band, Rhubarb & the Alternative Dudes. Amazing whiskey. Perfect birthday night out!

Great low-light atmosphere, giant whiskey selection, and no problems with the service. Menu was a bit limited for my unsophisticated pallette, but the hand pies were a delicious option! Would definitely go back for a light meal and conversation-type evening.

First time there. The bartenders were quite knowledgeable about the Scotch from Scotland and the Bourbons. Their recommendation based on our palate was perfect. Great ambiance, will definitely go back.
Every kind of whisky imaginable.
Had the short rib hand pockets and french onion soup. Both were fantastic.

An absolutely amazing place to end up or even start and stay with. The late night menu is absolutely delicious, their fries are crispy,  and the vegan mac and cheese is to die for. The pickle plate is both interesting and delicious! The wait staff checked in with us, and the atmosphere is so comfortable. I will absolutely come here again, and with friends too!
Good drinks live music. Nice evening although it's extremely difficult to have conversations over the volume of the band.
Drinks, Apps, burgers and steaks were great
Place gets busy but the drinks are fantastic but you certainly pay for them. The food is sub par.
Poor service, disorganized staff, but restaurant is very cozy, and attractive
Cozy, comfy, whiskey and super knowledgeable and friendly staff...Love it!

Great selection of whiskeys, especially bourbons, and friendly, knowledgeable staff. I will be returning to try the food as I've heard the burgers are very good. I went to hear an acoustic folk/rock duo and the only problem was the awkward set up/location for the musicians.
Oh my lord!!! We had oysters, followed by the bone marrow appetizer, then the elk entree and the chicken/bacon/leek pocket thing. Insanely tasty. Eat here and die happy!

An amazing whisky selection and a phenomenal Atmosphere. My only complaint was that it felt a bit understaffed to handle the Friday evening rush. Otherwise the food was phenomenal and the wiskey was supurb. I wish they had eye droppers to help dilute the whiskey otherwise great atmosphere, great bar, be sure to catch happy hour.
Awesome collection of spirits, knowledgeable bartenders, nice atmosphere. Sometimes live music, if that is your thing. And perfect location across from the Hyatt, should you be staying there.
Craft cocktail bar at its best!
Amazing menu. Best selection of liquors I've seen in Buffalo and major cities. Staff was very pleasant.
THE place to drink whiskey in Buffalo, so much choice and really knowledgeable staff!

Amazing whiskey bar right across the street from the Hyatt and around the block from the convention center. The selection of whiskeys in all price ranges is impressive.  The service is friendly and helpful, but it gets a little crowded on weekends after 10.
Great people! Great cocktails! Great food! Best oysters!

Of the three days I spent in Buffalo, two of them ended at the Lucky Day.  The spirit selection is outstanding and the staff is knowledge, un-pretentious and non-judgmental.  This place is a "must-see" for the casual drinker and the connoisseur alike.
Great selection of everything. Basil Hayden is a great whiskey to start with
Classy atmosphere.  Extensive collection of whiskey, bourbon and rye!

Only stopped in for one drink, I can't wait to return. One of the coolest old buildings downtown, so many unique features. I had and old fashioned, bartenders choice on the bourbon used, and it was good. Don't know what it cost me, but I'll have another. Hopefully soon.
Very high class, fancy bar. Great cocktails and a classy atmosphere. Prices aren't bad either for the upscale venue
Amazing atmosphere and bartenders
Exactly what a whiskey bar so. Dark wood, great drinks and knowledgeable bartenders. Phil mixed a stunning sazerac. Every town needs a place this good.

Love this bar. If they have the squash blossoms on the menu get them, they are fantastic! I much prefer sitting at the bar than at a table though, it tends to get really warm down in the restaurant area. But the food and drinks are always great, and the live music is always nice.
Live music , friendly staff, all by candle light.
Fantastic whiskey cocktails at the low-end of the price spectrum.  Bartenders show care and exceptional craftsmanship in the making of this swanky establishment's libations.  Vibes A++
Happy our is Manhattan's and old fashioned's which is awesome well mixed cocktails to die for hand (meat) pies cool atmosphere with 18" diameter beams.

Incredible whiskey selection, nice atmosphere, and good food. I went here on Wednesday while I was in town for work and sat at the bar. Good service, knowledgeable bartender, and a simple unpretentious menu.
Comfortable atmosphere and a good amount of seating. We got happy hour old fashions for $6 which was an excellent value and sat in front of the windows. They have an overwhelming amount of alcohol.
Prices are steep.  Best selection in Buffalo
Great whiskey selection, great service!
Great atmosphere overall very classy and chill

Loved this fun and unique bar!!  The bartenders know their stuff and don't try to push pricier bourbons... they really want you to have a fabulous experience! We went back every night we were in town!
Gavin has so much knowledge & very engaging

A revamp of what used to be Century Grill. Although they still kept the two tired seating structure and the general aesthetic of the rest of the place, the vibe feels classic and new at the same time. The cocktails were on point and they had an oyster special when I stopped in. Any place that makes a perfect sazarac is awesome in my books.
A well made whiskey sour really sets the mood. A+ stuff here.
loved this place. has a cool hipster vibe with live music, at least they did the Thursday night I was there.
Very good food. Great service. Live band. Like the layout of the place.
Classy whiskey bar with a vast selection!  Only stopped in for drinks this time but hopefully can stop back one day.

Didn't expect Buffalo to be so cool.  Lots of bars downtown and it was packed on a Saturday night.  This is just across from the Hyatt Regency and was our last stop... for over two hours!  Fantastic old bar back with a ladder and 500 plus bottles of rare liquor.  And great bartenders who can suggest what to try.  Lots of class from the good old days.
The only whiskey library in Buffalo with a small but expertly executed menu

The best back bar I have ever seen. The bar staff were both knowledgeable and friendly and made great suggestions for myself and my friend based on what we currently drank. I will be back and I recommend any whiskey drinker do the same.
Came for my birthday and enjoyed everything about our meal. I will be recommending to anyone and everyone!

One of my favorite spots in Buffalo!
Always a great place for whiskey and thrasher burgers! Best old fashion and Manhattan's you will ever have.

If you're after a wide variety of whiskey, this is certainly the place to get your fill. I will leave others to describe how accurate/knowledgeable the staff is, but I can say that you can get into a large bar tab with ease! Tasty!
Amazing cocktails and spirit selection! Food menu is small and a bit limited, but steak fries and scallop dinner were cooked nicely! Would highly recommended for drinks or a night cap.

Very disappointed with the staff here.  I originally gave this place an outstanding review, but it has definitely changed.  I was out for my birthday and my party of 17 stopped here for some drinks. I ordered a round to say thanks to my party and the bar made a drink that was not so great.  My guest wanted to return their drink in exchange for a glass of wine.  I asked for a glass of Chardonnay.  The bartender did not disclose how much this glass of wine was. There is a glass of Chardonnay on the menu for $8, which I was expecting.  The bartender poured a glass of their $28 a glass version without warning.  I got the bill and disputed the charge regarding this.  The bartender apologized, but did not correct his mistake.  He still charged me for both drinks. I'm upset with this staff because they did not fix their mistake and they should warn their customers that instead of the $8 dollar glass, the $28 glass is what they are pouring. I would have totally changed my selection before the pour. I hope they improve their customer relations soon because I did like coming to their location.  I often show up there with parties of 15 or larger.  Poor customer service.

Couldn’t find a reason not to give it any less than 5 stars. First time here but the service food atmosphere and drink were all great, and what is a restaurant but those four things? Looking forward to coming back for round two, bringing some friends, and seeing if my first impressions ring true again

Excellent food, great atmosphere.  We had the salmon which came with greens, a version of carmelized onions and two delicious sauces one a scallop cream.  We also loved the sirloin tips and fries, there was an excellent sauce with this dish also.  The coffee was really good, a little smoky and their eclair was split open and covered with fresh fruit.... Almost a healthy dessert.  A really excellent meal.  We plan to go back some time when we can try what looked like 300 choices of whiskey.
Decent food, with with an extraordinarily large and well priced liquor list.
